Access to Clean Drinking Water: A Global Challenge

Load Libraries

Code 
import pandas as pd
import plotnine as p9
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

Load Data

Code 
indicator_df = pd.read_csv("unicef_indicator_1.csv")
metadata_df = pd.read_csv("unicef_metadata.csv")

Data Preparation

Code 
# Filter for 'Proportion of population using piped drinking water'
water_df = indicator_df[
    indicator_df['indicator'].str.contains('piped drinking water', case=False, na=False)
]

# Get latest year data per country
latest_water_df = water_df.sort_values('time_period').drop_duplicates('country', keep='last')

World Map Visualization (with GeoPandas)

Code 
# Load a simple world map
world = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvkelso/natural-earth-vector/master/geojson/ne_110m_admin_0_countries.geojson')

# Merge world map with water data
world = world.merge(latest_water_df, left_on='NAME', right_on='country', how='left')

# Plot World Map
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(20, 10))
world.boundary.plot(ax=ax, linewidth=0.5, color='black')
world.plot(column='obs_value', cmap='Blues', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True)
ax.set_title('Global Access to Clean Drinking Water (%) - Latest Data', fontdict={'fontsize': 20})
ax.axis('off')
plt.show()

Bar Chart: Top 10 Countries with Highest Access

Code 
top10 = latest_water_df.nlargest(10, 'obs_value')

(p9.ggplot(top10, p9.aes(x='reorder(country, obs_value)', y='obs_value'))
 + p9.geom_col(fill='skyblue')
 + p9.coord_flip()
 + p9.theme_minimal()
 + p9.ggtitle('Top 10 Countries with Highest Access to Piped Drinking Water')
 + p9.xlab('Country')
 + p9.ylab('Access (%)'))

Scatter Plot with Regression Line (Year vs Access)

Code 
scatter_df = water_df[water_df['time_period'] >= 2010]

(p9.ggplot(scatter_df, p9.aes(x='time_period', y='obs_value'))
 + p9.geom_point(alpha=0.5)
 + p9.geom_smooth(method='lm', color='red')
 + p9.theme_minimal()
 + p9.ggtitle('Access to Piped Water Over Time (2010 onwards)')
 + p9.xlab('Year')
 + p9.ylab('Access (%)'))

Time Series Plot: Top 20 Countries Over Time

Code 
# Get Top 20 countries
top20_countries = latest_water_df.nlargest(20, 'obs_value')['country']

# Filter dataset
top20_timeseries_df = water_df[water_df['country'].isin(top20_countries)]

# Plot
(p9.ggplot(top20_timeseries_df, p9.aes(x='time_period', y='obs_value', color='country'))
 + p9.geom_line(size=1, alpha=0.8)
 + p9.theme_minimal()
 + p9.ggtitle('Access to Piped Drinking Water Over Time (Top 20 Countries)')
 + p9.xlab('Year')
 + p9.ylab('Access to Piped Water (%)'))
